Thanks — I’ve reviewed the HTML you posted for LinkNest. I can do a focused code update (fix accessibility, security, UX, and small JS improvements), refactor it into components (React/Vue), add a backend/affiliate redirect, or open a PR in the repo — which would you prefer?

Quick summary of issues and recommended priorities
- Accessibility / semantics
  - Missing alt attributes on images.
  - Search input missing accessible label.
  - Buttons that open external links should use anchors with rel="noopener noreferrer" (or explicitly sever window.opener).
  - Focus styles for keyboard users.
- Security / privacy
  - Use rel="noopener noreferrer" on external links to prevent tabnabbing.
  - Sanitize any user-provided affiliate link before opening.
- UX / behavior
  - Use debounced search for performance.
  - Use proper form controls with name attributes and type=submit for real submissions.
  - Consider rendering product data from JSON so the UI is data-driven.
- SEO / metadata
  - Add meta description.
  - Ensure language and title are correct (you already have lang attribute and title).
- Progressive enhancement & performance
  - Consider using a manifest and a simple service worker for offline caching.
  - Use lazy-loading for product images (loading="lazy").
- Analytics & tracking
  - Add click tracking (server-side redirect preferred to keep affiliate strings private).
- Data integrity / admin flow
  - Form should POST to an admin endpoint and have validation + sanitization.

If you want a small, immediately-usable patch, here’s an improved index.html with the most important fixes (accessibility, security, search debounce, lazy images, semantic form fields, and safer external links). If you want, I can open this as a PR to the repo.

